article.linkText: SIU-Edwardsville downs SE Missouri St 86-86 in triple OT
article.story: CAPRE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- David McFarland scored 21 points and Cameron Williams blocked Isaiah Gable's shot attempt with a second left and SIU-Edwardsville beat Southeast Missouri State 87-86 in triple overtime Thursday night. McFarland made a pair of free throws and a jump shot to open the final overtime and the Cougars (6-13, 2-5 Ohio Valley Conference) never trailed from there. Nygal Russell made 1 of 2 foul shots with 3:07 left in the second overtime to tie it at 78-apiece before the two teams combined to miss the last seven shot attempts and committed three turnovers. The Redhawks' Sage Tolbert tied it at 76-all with a layup as time expired to send it into a second overtime. Cameron Williams' layup with 67 seconds left in regulation tied it 68-all for the Cougars and neither team scored again. Tyresse Williford scored 18 points, Brandon Jackson had 18 points with 15 rebounds and Williams scored 13 for the Cougars who were 28 of 85 (33 percent) from the field. Ledarrius Brewer led the Red Hawks (6-14, 1-6) with 24 points and Gabe McGlothan and Tolbert each scored 18.
